Source: dropbear
Section: core
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Mikhail Gusarov <dottedmag@dottedmag.net>
XCS-Cross-Host-Build-Depends: debhelper
XCS-Cross-Build-Depends: libz1-dev
Build-Depends: debhelper, zlib1g-dev
Standards-Version: 3.8.3

Package: dropbear
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: lightweight SSH2 server and client
 dropbear is a SSH 2 server and client designed to be small enough to
 be used in small memory environments, while still being functional and
 secure enough for general use.
 .
 It implements most required features of the SSH 2 protocol, and other
 features such as X11 and authentication agent forwarding.
 .
 See http://matt.ucc.asn.au/dropbear/dropbear.html

Package: dropbear-utils
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Suggests: dropbear
Description: lightweight SSH2 server and client -- utilities
 dropbear is a SSH 2 server and client designed to be small enough to
 be used in small memory environments, while still being functional and
 secure enough for general use.
 .
 It implements most required features of the SSH 2 protocol, and other
 features such as X11 and authentication agent forwarding.
 .
 This package contains dropbearconvert tool suitable to convert host- and
 userkeys from and to OpenSSH format.

Package: dropbear-dbg
Architecture: any
Section: debug
Depends: dropbear (= ${binary:Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: lightweight SSH2 server and client -- debug package
 dropbear is a SSH 2 server and client designed to be small enough to
 be used in small memory environments, while still being functional and
 secure enough for general use.
 .
 It implements most required features of the SSH 2 protocol, and other
 features such as X11 and authentication agent forwarding.
 .
 This package contains debugging symbols.
